## Inputs and Outputs

| Action (WS) | Payload Expected | Action Taken / Output Response |
|-------------|------------------|--------------------------------|
| `dmx/start_learn` | `{"parameter": "deck_a.opacity"}` | Enters learn mode for parameter. |
| `dmx/stop_learn`  | `{}` | Exits learn mode. |
| `dmx/add_mapping` | `{"parameter": "...", "channel": 1}` | Creates and saves a new mapping. |
| `dmx/remove_mapping`| `{"id": "uuid..."}` | Deletes mapping. |
| `dmx/input` (outgoing)| `{"channel": 1, "value": 255}` | Emitted when a DMX value changes. |
| `dmx/mapping_created` (outgoing)| `{"id": "...", "parameter": "...", ...}` | Emitted when learn completes successfully. |

---

## Edge Cases and Error Handling

- What happens if `start_learn` is called while already learning another parameter? → The previous learn session is aborted/overwritten, and a warning is logged.
- What happens if a DMX mapping points to an invalid parameter? → It is safely ignored at runtime, but logs a debug message.
- What happens if the WebSocket disconnects during a learn session? → The learn mode should ideally time out or be explicitly reset on reconnect.

